description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a physiotherapist to join the acute and ambulatory care paediatric physiotherapy team working in the North Hampshire area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caseload includes children and young people aged 0 -19 with a variety of conditions (respiratory, orthopaedic, MSK, neonatal) providing both challenges and opportunities to develop and strengthen experience and skills in the paediatric field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with other team members in a variety of settings including: acute in patient wards, day-case unit, diagnostic and treatment centre, neonatal unit, outpatient clinics, satellite community clinics, hydrotherapy and gym.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As many children are seen jointly with other professionals including Consultant Paediatricians, Occupational Therapists and Nurses in clinic and treatment settings, the ability to work well within a multi-professional team is essential. There is also a well-established programme of therapy led clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position offers educational and clinical support and CPD is actively encouraged with a strong programme of multi-professional in-service training and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to a car for business use and a current UK driving licence is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
